This paper deals with image-to-image translation, which is a computer vision problem, hence it is most likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also proposes a new approach that involves instance-level translation, which involves fine-grained local styles, and global styles, which are likely to be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions a benchmark dataset, which could be related to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
